    %h2 Ways You Can Get to Know Students

    %div
      %img{:src => "/images/en_badges/tours_and_talks.jpg"}
      %p
        %strong Tours & Talks
      %p Give students a tour of your offices and then sit down for 15-20 minutes to chat about the work your developers are doing, your office’s own unique culture and style, and what kinds of developers and skills you typically look for when hiring.

    %div
      %img{:src => "/images/en_badges/social_hour.jpg"}
      %p
        %strong Social Hour
      %p Host a lunch or happy hour with students. This could be combined with a tour and is a fun way to socialize and get to know the students. Students can also get to know your team and get excited about your company.

    %div
      %img{:src => "/images/en_badges/swag.jpg"}
      %p
        %strong Share Some Swag
      %p Dress the students in your company’s gear! Our students are actively engaged in networking events all over town every single week. Wouldn’t it be great if they were wearing your logo while they meet people all over town?

    %div
      %img{:src => "/images/en_badges/guest_lecture.jpg"}
      %p
        %strong Guest Lecture
      %p We welcome your expertise! Is there a topic your team values above all else that you want to make sure students know? There is room in the class schedule for a brief lecture or talk on topics that matter most to you.


